## OpenClaw — Control Plane Detail

### Gateway
- Protocol: WebSocket (`ws://`) + HTTP
- Bind: loopback only (`127.0.0.1:18789`)
- Auth: token from file (`~/.openclaw/credentials/gateway-token.txt`)
- Control UI allowed origins: `http://localhost:18789`, `http://127.0.0.1:18789`
- Node identity: `new-node-123` ("Esteban's MacBook Pro")

The gateway is the sole ingress point for external tool connections (Codex, browser, dashboard) and serves the webchat UI.

### Router / Bindings
Agent routing is defined in `openclaw.json` under `bindings`. The full routing table:

| Channel        | Account/Condition        | Agent    |
|---------------|--------------------------|----------|
| telegram       | account: default (hermes-bot) | hermes |
| telegram       | account: vicky           | vicky    |
| telegram       | account: cal             | Cal      |
| discord        | (any)                    | Cal      |
| webchat        | (any)                    | Cal      |

Telegram has three separate bots, each mapped to a different agent. This means a user must message the correct bot to reach the intended agent.

### ACP (Agent Control Panel)
- Enabled: `true`
- Default agent: `hermes`
- Allowed agents: `hermes`, `Cal`, `codex`, `laura`, `tony`, `codegen`, `qa`, `outbound-sales`

The ACP is an internal control surface for directing agent execution. The `acpx` plugin appears to extend it.

### Agent-to-Agent Messaging
Enabled for: `hermes`, `Cal`, `vicky`, `prodeng`, `tony`, `laura`, `ops`, `revenue`, `intel`, `qa`, `codegen`, `outbound-sales`.

Note: Hermes workspace `MEMORY.md` contains a single-line note: *"Agent-to-agent messaging is disabled. Re-assign and re-prioritize agent tasks manually via Paperclip board."* — This conflicts with the `agentToAgent.enabled: true` config. Current operational state is ambiguous.

### Cron System
- Config: `~/.openclaw/cron/jobs.json` (1955-line JSON, version 1)
- Max concurrent runs: 1
- Each job defines: `id`, `name`, `enabled`, `schedule` (cron expression + timezone), `agentId`, `payload` (agentTurn with message and model), `delivery` (channel, target), `sessionTarget` (isolated), `wakeMode`
- Cron sessions are isolated by default

Key active jobs:
- `behavioral-governance-maintenance` — Weekly (Sundays 18:00 ET), Cal, governance review, Telegram delivery
- `Monitor NYC 311 (Weekends)` — Weekends 09:00 ET, Vicky, web fetch of NYC 311 portal, alert Grace on Telegram if parking/school status changes
- Multiple other jobs (total 79KB of job definitions)

### Hook System
Internal hooks (configured in `openclaw.json`):
- `boot-md` — runs at boot
- `command-logger` — logs all commands
- `session-memory` — handles session memory on close/open

### Plugin System
Active plugins: `opik-openclaw` (v0.2.9, from local path), `acpx`, `ollama`, `openrouter`.
Allowed plugin list includes 30+ providers (Anthropic, OpenAI, Google, Mistral, etc.) — most are enabled but not necessarily active.

