## Data Flow — Inbound Message

```
Telegram message → OpenClaw gateway (WS:18789)
    → Router applies bindings → selects agent
    → Agent session starts (or resumes)
    → Workspace files bootstrapped (SOUL, IDENTITY, AGENTS, MEMORY, daily notes)
    → Agent processes message
    → Tool calls (web, file, shell, agent-to-agent, Paperclip)
    → Response generated
    → Delivery queue → Telegram reply (or announce mode for cron)
```

## Data Flow — Cron Job

```
Cron scheduler reads jobs.json
    → At scheduled time, creates isolated agent session
    → Sends payload message to agent
    → Agent executes (with lightContext = minimal bootstrap)
    → Output routed per delivery config (announce/none/telegram)
    → Session closed, state.lastRunAtMs updated in jobs.json
```

